                       Squidger V2, SQGShow and SQGView
                       ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
    
þ
        This is an excellent graphics compaction system created by Paul
    Burkey, which crunches IFF, and SPack pictures down further than what
    the standard SPack does. There are 7 different kinds of crunching you
    can choose from, to best suit your compaction needs, ranging from a
    left-right pack, and even a plane pack. The SQGShow and SQGView allow
    you to look at your work. For the source code to the unpacking
    routines, so that you can use them in your own programs, look in the
    GRAPHICS section in the library, for the file PB_UNSQG.AMOS. You must
    have Paul's permission first before you can use his system.
    
